PBS.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Centrifuge at 1,000 rpm for 5 minutes at 4\u00b0C.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Resuspend the pellet with slow pipetting in 1 ml of Lysis Buffer B (10 mM Tris-HCl pH 8, 140 mM NaCl, 1.5 mM MgCl2, 0.5 % NP-40).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Centrifuge at 1,000 g for 3 minutes at 4\u00b0C.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Resuspend the pellet with slow pipetting in 1 ml of Lysis Buffer B and transfer to an ice-cold 14 ml round-bottom tube.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add drop by drop 100 \u03bcl of the Detergent Stock Solution (3.3 % (w\/v) sodium deoxycholate, 6.6 % (v\/v) Tween 40) under slow vortexing.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Transfer to a fresh ice-cold 1.5 ml tube. Centrifuge at 1,000 g for 3 minutes at 4\u00b0C.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Resuspend the pellet with slow pipetting in 1 ml of Lysis Buffer B.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Centrifuge at 1,000 g for 3 minutes at 4\u00b0C.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Resuspend the pellet in 1 ml of TRIzol using a 21-gauge syringe and incubated 5 minutes at room temperature.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add 200 \u03bcl of chloroform and vortex the sample vigorously for 15 seconds.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Centrifuge at 12,000 g for 15 minutes at 4\u00b0C.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Transfer the aqueous fraction to a new tube containing 580 \u03bcl of isopropanol.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Incubate 10 minutes at room temperature.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Centrifuge at 12,000 g for 10 minutes at 4\u00b0C.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Remove most of the supernatant with a 1 ml pipette.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Centrifuge at 12,000 g for one minute at 4\u00b0C.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Remove the remaining liquid with a 10 or 20 \u03bcl tip.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Resuspend the pellet in 87 \u03bcl of RNase-free water, 10 \u03bcl of 10 \u00d7 DNase buffer, 2 \u03bcl of DNase I, and 1 \u03bcl of RNase OUT.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Incubate for 30 minutes at 32\u00b0C.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add 100 \u03bcl of acid-phenol:chloroform pH 4.2.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Vortex 10 seconds, then centrifuge 5 minutes at 13,000 rpm at room temperature. <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Transfer the upper phase to a new tube and add 100 \u03bcl of acid-phenol:chloroform pH 4.2.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Vortex 10 seconds, then centrifuge 5 minutes at 13,000 rpm at room temperature. <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Transfer the upper phase to a new tube and add 250 \u03bcl of 100% ethanol, 10 \u03bcl of NaOAc, and 1 \u03bcl of Glycoblue (or 1 \u03bcl of glycogen 10 mg\/ml).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Invert the tube several times and incubate at -20\u00b0C for at least two hours (or overnight).<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Centrifuge for 20 minutes at 13,000 rpm at 4\u00b0C.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Remove the supernatant and centrifuge for two minutes at 13,000 rpm at 4\u00b0C.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Remove the last drops, air dry for 1-2 minutes, and resuspend in 20 ul of RNase-free water.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Determine the concentration and the 260\/280 and 260\/230 ratios using a NanoDrop or another system.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Perform the cDNA reaction for qRT-PCR or NGS.<\/li><\/ol><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Protocol for purifying nuclear RNA for qRT-PCR or next generation sequencing analysis.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1632243361}